It is often naturalized in our yards for ornamental cultivation. The feathery leaves of the Wild Tansy are lovely, especially when growing in abundance on marshy ground, and it has a more rejuvenating aroma than the Garden Tansy.

Tansy will prosper in virtually any soil and might be increased, either in spring or fall, by slips or by dividing the sneaking roots, which if permitted to continue to be undisturbed, will, in a short time, overspread the ground. When transplanting the slips or sections of root, area therefore at least a foot apart.

The name Tansy is probably derived from the Greek Athanaton, either, says Dodoens, because it lasts so long in flower or, as Ambrosius thought, because it is capital for preserving dead bodies from corruption. It was said to have been given to Ganymede to make him never-ceasing.

Tansy was one of the Strewing Herbs mentioned by Tusser in 1577, and was one of the native plants dedicated to the Virgin Mary.

Perhaps it found additional favor as a 'Strewing Herb' because it was said to be effectual in keeping flies away, particularly if mixed with senior leaves.

Parkinson grew Tansy amongst other aromatic and culinary herbs in his garden.

It is connected with some interesting old customs observed at Easter time, when even archbishops and bishops played handball with men of their congregation, and a Tansy cake was the reward of the victors. These Tansy cakes were made from the young leaves of the plant, mixed with eggs, and were thought to purify the humors of the body after the limited fare of Lent. In time, this custom obtained a kind of symbolism, and Tansies, as these cakes were called, became eaten on Easter Day as a remembrance of the bitter herbs consumed by the Jews at the Passover. Coles (1656) states the beginning of eating it in the spring is because Tansy is very wholesome after the salt fish eaten during Lent, and counteracts the ill-effects which the 'moist and cold constitution of winter has actually made on people ... though many understand it not, and some basic individuals take it for a matter of superstition to do so.'.

This balsamic plant, states Boerhaave, will supply the place of nutmegs and cinnamon, and the young leaves, shredded, act as a flavoring for puddings and omelets. Gerard informs us that Tansy Teas were extremely respected in Lent as well as Tansy puddings.

description:
Avance del Proyecto de Innovación Docente de la UGR titulado: "Adherencia a la dieta baja en fenilalanina en niños con Fenilcetonuria (PKU) y aprendizaje de sus características mediante el uso de juegos multimedia". 
La finalidad de este proyecto es la elaboración de un juego multimedia educativo para niños con fenilcetonuria. Estará disponible para las plataformas: XBOX 360, Iphone y ordenador. 
Es un proyecto internacional y sin ánimo de lucro en el que además de la UGR están involucradas otras Universidades, instituciones, fundaciones y empresas privadas. Colaboran en el proyecto: la Fundación Alicia, el Consejo General de Colegios Oficiales de Psicólogos de España, FX Animation, Psicofundación, Nutricia, Ediciones Cuarentaicuatro, el Hospital Infantil de Birmingham (Reino Unido), el Hospital Sainte Justine de Montreal (Canadá), el Departamento de Psiquiatría de la Universidad de Harvard (Estados Unidos) y el Centro Kennedy de Copenhague (Dinamarca).
Cuenta además con el auspicio de numerosas entidades médicas y científicas como la Asociación Española para el Estudio de los Errores Congénitos del Metabolismo.
El juego, desarrollado por la empresa FX Animation de Barcelona, estará disponible en inglés, danés y español y será distribuido de forma gratuita en Dinamarca, Canadá, Massachusetts, Reino Unido y España. Actualmente se baraja la posibilidad de traducirlo al francés y al catalán.
El proyecto cuenta para su introducción y contextualización con un cortometraje dirigido por el melillense afincado en Barcelona Santiago Moga, que fue íntegramente rodado en la sede de la Fundación Alicia. La música original del juego y la película ha sido compuesta por el grupo madrileño After Disaster y el compositor cordobés Miguel Galadí. El vídeo musical para la promoción del proyecto es obra del grupo WTF.
title: Trailer del juego Salvar al Planeta PKU (Save the PKU Planet)

description:
Do you know someone who is too manipulative and full of himself? Does someone you know charm the masses yet lack the ability to deeply connect with those around her?

Grandiosity and exaggerated self-worth. Pathological lying. Manipulation. Lack of remorse. Shallowness. Exploitation for financial gain. These are the qualities of Almost Psychopaths. They are not the deranged criminals or serial killers that might be coined "psychopaths" in the movies or on TV. They are spouses, coworkers, bosses, neighbors, and people in the news who exhibit many of the same behaviors as a full-blown psychopath, but with less intensity and consistency.
In Almost a Psychopath, Ronald Schouten, MD, JD, and James Silver, JD, draw on scientific research and their own experiences to help you identify if you are an Almost Psychopath and, if so, guide you to interventions and resources to change your behavior.

description:
At Best Drug Rehabilitation, we believe that helping people recover from substance abuse is just one part of a much bigger picture. Through community events, youth functions and charitable contributions, our goal is to reach out to others by carrying our message of recovery wherever we can. One such event, the Celebrate Recovery Walk, was held recently in Grand Rapids, MI to raise awareness about treatment for chemical dependency. Carrying signs with slogans like “Recovery Matters” and “Treatment is Effective”, several of the clients and staff members from BDR participated to show support for those who are struggling with addiction to drugs and alcohol.

Dr. Billy Taylor, one of the guest speakers at the walk, is the founder of Get Back Up, Inc., a non-profit service organization that addresses many of the challenges facing young adults in recovery. After giving an inspirational speech following the walk, he found a few minutes to sit with us and talk about the importance of events like this one. “I love sharing my message of recovery,” he tells us, “just to help them to know that there’s life on the other side of addiction.” In his speech, he compared substituting one drug for another to changing seats on an airplane that is crashing.

Like many of the course facilitators and counselors at BDR, Dr. Taylor can relate to people suffering from addiction on a personal level. He has had firsthand experience with recovery from drug abuse and alcoholism, and has been substance free for over 17 years. His personal testimony and knowledge about life under the influence helps him to connect with others and spread his message more effectively.

By participating in community events like the Celebrate Recovery Walk, our clients can find support and encouragement in their own personal recovery from substance abuse. “Dr. Taylor’s speech was really great because I could really relate to it,” says Tayla, a Best Drug Rehabilitation client. “I would always try to substitute my addictions and that just doesn’t work.” At our treatment facility, we help our clients to overcome their chemical dependency by discovering and addressing the underlying causes of their addiction rather than just treating the symptoms. In doing so, they build a stronger foundation in recovery and enjoy long term substance free living. They find a greater sense of self-confidence and hope for a brighter future. They find peace and happiness inside themselves.

description:
Midsummer Night's Dreaming is a one-off digital theatre project and our 40th interpretation of Shakespeare's A Midsummer Night's Dream a tale of love, fairies and mischief. 

Billy Shakespeare and his pig Francis can tell you more about the story.

Across Midsummer weekend (21 -- 23 June) the play will be performed by an acting company in real time, directed by our Artistic Director Gregory Doran, culminating in a wedding, which you can attend. More information about the live events and the cast will be released shortly.

Meanwhile, the story will be shared through photos, snippets and news stories online from the perspectives of some lesser known characters, as if it was happening in real life. Where ever you are in the world you can watch the play unfold via some clever technology on our website, and we are inviting you to share your take on the production.

Find out more at http:// www.rsc.org.uk/dreaming and follow the RSC on Google+ http://google.com/+royalshakespearecompany
title: Midsummer Night's Dreaming | Billy trailer | Royal Shakespeare Company

description:
Vegetarian Collard Greens? Yes you read that right! I've been trying to cook healthier meals these days. As much as I love soul food, I simply can't eat the "traditional" styles of it as much as I'd like. Greens have always been a favorite of mine. Usually I use smoked meat to flavor my greens, but as we all know- smoked meats are exactly the healthiest thing to put in our bodies. Most smoked meats are cured with lots of salt and sugar, and plenty of other things we probably shouldn't indulge in on a regular basis.

Here is a really easy recipe for collard greens that don't require any meat nor a lot of time. I find this recipe to be perfect on those busy work night, but still suitable for a easy Sunday night dinner
http://www.iheartrecipes.com/vegetarian-collard-greens/





I Heart Recipes is a channel full of soul food, and other delicious family favored recipes. All of the recipes are beginner friendly, and recipes are accessible at http://www.iheartrecipes.com.
The channel is hosted by myself, Rosie Willis. I am a family woman who enjoys cooking and baking. I am not a trained professional cook. I was taught how to cook by my mother, and many aunts.

Kinostart / Filmstart von The Descendants: 26. Januar 2012 im Kino.

Deine Gedanken ueber den Trailer und The Descendants Filmkritik Review mit George Clooney und Shailene Woodley?


Franc's Twitter: http://twitter.com/FilmKritikTV2


Matt King (George Clooney), Vater zweier Töchter, ist gezwungen, seine Vergangenheit zu überdenken und neu zu bewerten, als seine Frau nach einem Speed-Boat-Unfall vor dem Strand von Waikiki ins Koma fällt. Unbeholfen versucht er, die Beziehung zu seinen Töchtern, der altklugen 10-jährigen Scottie (Amara Miller) und der rebellischen 17-jährigen Alexandra (Shailene Woodley), wieder zu verbessern, während er gleichzeitig mit der Entscheidung ringt, ob er den Grundbesitz seiner Familie verkaufen soll. Von Mitgliedern der hawaiianischen Königsfamilie und Missionaren haben die Kings vor Generationen unschätzbar wertvolles Land erhalten, das zu den letzten unberührten tropischen Strandabschnitten auf den Inseln gehört.

Als Alexandra die Bombe platzen lässt und enthüllt, dass ihre Mutter zum Zeitpunkt des Unfalls mitten in einer Affäre mit einem anderen Mann steckte, muss Matt innerhalb einer Woche voller wichtiger Entscheidungen sein Leben, ganz zu schweigen von seinem Vermächtnis, plötzlich mit völlig anderen Augen betrachten.

Mit seinen Töchtern im Schlepptau begibt er sich relativ planlos auf die Suche nach dem Liebhaber seiner Frau. Unterwegs, nach Begegnungen der komischen, ärgerlichen und transzendenten Art, wird ihm bewusst, dass er endlich den richtigen Kurs eingeschlagen hat, um sein Leben und seine Familie neu zu ordnen.

description:
"Someone Else's Forward Motion" from Synecdoche, New York by Jon Brion can be licensed through the Score Revolution website. http://bit.ly/15HxWWE

Oscar-winning screenwriter Charlie Kaufman's acclaimed, controversial directing debut stars Philip Seymour Hoffman as a struggling theater director who undertakes an ambitious magnum opus that quickly begins to consume his entire reality. 

The vacillating line between genius and madness seems inexorably at work in Jon Brion's eclectic, stylistically and instrumentally diverse score, which has some marginal kinship with his previous work for the Kaufman-scripted, Michel Gondry-directed Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind. At times resolutely classical, elsewhere Jazz-affected, at other times unapologetically avant-gardist and experimental, Brion's score appears to follow only one general rule, to capture the chaos of an unbridled, increasingly untamable psyche. Pervasively melancholic yet profoundly astute in its attention to instrumental detail, Brion's score most flowers when embracing the unconventional: the soulful three-part "Piano One," "Piano Two" and "Piano Three"; the boozy lounge songs "Little Person" and "Song for Caden"; the music hall throwback chorus of "Schenectady"; the soul-searing sadness of "Still Can't Return (Still Trying)" all playing their part in this smart musical underscore to Kaufman's symphony of uncertainty.
title: Synecdoche, New York - Jon Brion - "Someone Else's Forward Motion"

description:
There are 2 species of  Swallow-wort that are growing and taking over the natural landscape in New York State. Black or Louis' swallow-wort (previously Vincetoxicum nigrum and Cynanchum nigrum) is a perennial, twining herbaceous vine. And Pale Swallow-wort (Vincetoxicum rossicum; syn. Cynanchum rossicum)is a perennial, twining herbaceous vine also.
Black Swallowort is Native to Europe, and Pale swallowwort is native to the Ukraine.
Both Species are self-compatible, Plants can produce up to 1700 seeds per seed cluster. Wind and animals are the main method of seeddispersal. Seeds survive in soil more than 2 years. Germinate best when at 2.5 centimeters or less. The plants produce 4 to 6 bract Rizomes, When removing swallowort dig don't pull this plant can go down a ft or more, you must dig out every bract of the rizome or the same plant will come back.
title: Tackling the invasive Swallow Wort

American Urethane created this polyurethane suspension bushing for the automotive Industry. Polyurethane suspension bushings are used instead to plastic or rubber bushings because of their superior performance and long wear. In addition, these automotive bushings can be custom designed for each type of vehicle or usage. Hardness can be rigid or soft. Colors can be unique and selected by the client. 

Custom Polyurethane for Automotive Parts

Our company creates custom polyurethane parts and components for the automotive industry including 

• Polyurethane Suspension Bushings
• Polyurethane Transmission Mounts
• Polyurethane Motor Mounts
• Polyurethane Gears
• Polyurethane Seals
• Polyurethane Springs

All of these polyurethane components are designed to exacting standards. Each client project always begins with rapidly built prototypes created at low cost for evaluation and testing. We are happy to manufacture both short or long term product runs. 

Polyurethane Superior To Plastic, Metal and Rubber

Polyurethane component parts are used by the automotive industry because polyurethane is superior to other materials such as plastic and rubber. Molded polyurethane parts offer high load and high compression abilities that function long after rubber and plastic parts have failed. Cast polyurethane parts can be made iron-strong or sponge-soft, in any color or shape. In addition, polyurethane components offer long run durability and extreme resistance to harsh environments of water, heat, solvents, chemicals and abrasion.

Tiranë – Paskal Milo, Pëllumb Xhufi, Kristo Frashëri dhe të tjerë historianë që e kanë shkruar njëherë historinë sipas oreksit të Enver Hoxhës nuk kanë asnjë të drejtë morale ta rishkruajnë atë. Madje, veprat e tyre duhen flakur nga libraritë apo bibliotekat në rastin kur bëjnë thirrje nostaligjike për rikthimin e Enver Hoxhës.
I këtij mendimi është Agron Tufa, Drejtor i Institutit të Studimeve të Krimit dhe Pasojave të Komunizmit. Në një intervistë në “Ora News”, i pyetur për ndikimin e politikës në histori dhe rishkrimin e historisë, Tufa tha:
“Mendoj se politika gjithmonë duhet të qëndrojë larg çdo lloj shkence, se shkencat me politikën nuk kanë ndonjë gjë të përbashkët, por politika duhet të stimulojë, të mbështesë mendimin e ri shkencor dhe konkretisht, për shkencën e historisë ose shkencat humanitare, në të cilat jemi të zhytur deri në buzë në ideologjinë komuniste; duhet që të krijojë sa më shumë alternativa për ta thyer këtë linjë kompakte, që sundon institucionet e ku bën shkencat e historisë, universitetet. Dmth, katedrat e universiteteve, Akademinë e Shkencave. Këta nuk kanë asnjë arsye për të vazhduar t’i mëshojnë asaj pune që e kanë bërë përpara vitit 1990.

Për më shumë klikoni në http://www.oranews.tv/

China Glaze - Liquid Leather
5 oz paper cup
Room temperature filtered water

Step-by-Step
-Start out by cleaning your nails & prepping with a base coat

-Create a bullseye with both colors
-Draw in the design with the tip of your tool
-Dip you nail(s) into the design
-Clean the top of the water
-Slowly pull your nail out

description:
"  

0800000 - Nuclear Film Declassification Project / Nuclear Testing Review - 25:00 - Color - The U.S. Department of Energy (DOE) has embarked on the Nuclear Weapons Film Declassification Project to make available to the public and many users films that contain historically significant events in the development of the U.S. nuclear weapons program. This is being done under the Department of Energy's Openness Initiative. The film project is being carried out by DOE's Albuquerque Operations Office (AL) in cooperation with the U.S. Department of Defense (DoD).

Coming out of World War II, the U.S. and its allies realized they were in a Cold War with the Soviet Union. The first atomic bomb had been tested successfully at the Trinity Site in southeastern New Mexico in July 1945 and the second and third bombs were dropped on Hiroshima and Nagasaki, Japan, in August 1945, bringing about a speedy end to World War II. U.S. officials knew that the Soviet Union was on a fast track to develop the "bomb" and that they must develop more sophisticated nuclear weapons to stay ahead of the Soviet Union in the Cold War.

With the backing of the Executive Branch and Congress, the Army's Manhattan Engineer District (MED), which designed, developed and tested the first atomic bomb, embarked on a nuclear testing program in 1946 at the newly established Pacific Proving Ground in the Marshall Islands area. The MED was dissolved in 1947 and its duties and functions were given to the U.S. Atomic Energy Commission (AEC). The DoD joined the AEC in Joint Task Forces which continued the atmospheric testing program. This program allowed rapid gains in knowledge about weapons development, military effects, fallout and radiation effects, biomedical science, nuclear science, and delivery systems.

AL, a field office of the AEC, opened the Nevada Proving Ground northwest of Las Vegas, Nevada, in 1951 to reduce the cost of nuclear testing. The cost of transporting supplies, scientific gear, and materials for housing and testing, and for keeping a work force in the Pacific was monumental. The name of the Nevada Proving Ground was changed in 1957 to the Nevada National Security Site.

In hindsight, the AEC and the DoD made many mistakes in the testing program, such as underestimating the effects of fallout and deploying troops in areas of excessive radiation. Despite the errors in the early testing efforts, the U.S. surged ahead of all other nations in nuclear weapons capabilities, and gained the expertise which now sets the standard for what is "safe."

Although the Soviet Union mounted a massive attempt to gain a distinct advantage in nuclear military power, the U.S. maintained a deterrent to nuclear aggression. The U.S. now has a smaller but more sophisticated nuclear weapons stockpile, which the DOE manages jointly with the DoD. Through treaties, nuclear testing has been discontinued."
http://www.nv.doe.gov/library/films/fulltext/0800000.aspx
title: Nuclear Testing Review

description:
Remedios caseros para la indigestion o empacho - Como aliviar la dispepsia. También conocido como indigestión, empacho o malestar estomacal, es un término que describe el malestar o dolor en el abdomen superior. No es una enfermedad. La dispepsia es un grupo de síntomas que a menudo son distensión abdominal, náuseas y eructos. La indigestión es generalmente causada cuando el ácido del estómago entra en contacto con la mucosa del aparato digestivo - el revestimiento de protección sensible del sistema digestivo. Los ácidos del estómago descomponen la mucosa, causando irritación y la inflamación, lo que desencadena los síntomas de la indigestión. En la mayoría de los casos de indigestión se vincula a comer y / o beber. A veces puede ser causado por infección o algunos medicamentos.

Remedios caseros para la indigestion o empacho - Como aliviar la dispepsia

¿Cuáles son los síntomas de la indigestión?

La mayoría de las personas con indigestión sienten dolor y molestias en el estómago o en el pecho. La sensación general aparece poco después de consumir comida o bebida. En algunos casos, los síntomas pueden aparecer un tiempo después de una comida. Algunas personas se sienten llenas durante una comida, incluso si no han comido mucho. La acidez estomacal y la indigestión son dos condiciones distintas.

Remedios caseros para la indigestion o empacho - Como aliviar la dispepsia

La acidez es una sensación de ardor detrás del esternón, por lo general después de comer, los siguientes síntomas también son comunes:

Náusea

Eructos

Sentirse inflado (muy lleno)

En casos muy raros la indigestión puede ser un síntoma de cáncer de estómago. La indigestión leve rara vez es algo de qué preocuparse. Debes ver a tu médico si los síntomas continúan por más de dos semanas. Consulta a tu médico de inmediato si el dolor es intenso, y lo siguiente también se produce:

Pérdida del apetito o pérdida de peso

Vómitos

Heces negras

Ictericia (coloración amarillenta de los ojos y la piel)

Dolor en el pecho cuando te esfuerzas

Dificultad para respirar

Sudación

Radiación dolor en el pecho a la mandíbula, el brazo o el cuello

Remedios caseros para la indigestion o empacho - Como aliviar la dispepsia

¿Cuáles son las causas de la indigestión?

La indigestión suele estar relacionada con el estilo de vida y lo que comemos y bebemos. También puede ser causado por infección o algunas otras condiciones digestivas. Algunas causas comunes incluyen:

Comer demasiado

Comer demasiado rápido

El consumo de grasas o grasosas

El consumo de alimentos picantes

El consumo excesivo de cafeína

El consumo excesivo de alcohol

El consumo excesivo de chocolate

Consumir demasiadas bebidas gaseosas

El trauma emocional

Los cálculos biliares

La gastritis (inflamación del estómago)

Hernia de hiato

Infección, especialmente con una bacteria denominada Helicobacter pylori

Nerviosismo

Obesidad - causada por una mayor presión dentro del abdomen

Pancreatitis (inflamación del páncreas)

Las úlceras pépticas

De fumar

Algunos medicamentos, como los antibióticos y los AINE (medicamentos anti-inflamatorios no esteroideos)

El cáncer de estómago
title: Remedios caseros para la indigestion o empacho - Como aliviar la dispepsia
